[{"question":"What is the reaction of the Afghani people to this announcement by the president?","answer":"To be honest, it\u0027s hard to tell.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":35,"aSentId":36},{"question":"I mean aren\u0027t the Taliban just waiting in the mountains for the American troops to pull out and just to get back to what they did before?","answer":"You make a good point there, Piers.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":47,"aSentId":48},{"question":"Or hasn\u0027t it really been a counterterrorist operation that will now continue with more emphasis on Afghan troops than American troops?","answer":"Well, not really.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":65,"aSentId":66},{"question":"Have they?","answer":"No, they really haven\u0027t.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":72,"aSentId":73},{"question":"So isn\u0027t he entitled to remind the American people that it was a pretty successful mission, that it got rid of a pretty awful man?","answer":"But he didn\u0027t do it.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":84,"aSentId":85},{"question":"What is the historical significance of the president\u0027s visit to Afghanistan tonight and the speech he\u0027s made outlining the future there?","answer":"Well, I think it\u0027s very important.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":103,"aSentId":104},{"question":"What did you think?","answer":"No, he didn\u0027t get into, you know, a lot of politic -- political talk if you will in this 10-minute address he gave to the nation from the Bagram Air Base.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":134,"aSentId":135},{"question":"Let me turn to you, Doug Brinkley, I mean is that a fair criticism of the president, do you think, that he\u0027s just -- really this is just cheap politics?","answer":"No, it\u0027s cheap politics.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":150,"aSentId":151},{"question":"What was your reaction to that quote there from the Senate Armed Services Committee member?","answer":"Well, that was over the top.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":165,"aSentId":166},{"question":"Has America really got more out of this whole conflict in Afghanistan than the Soviets did?","answer":"That\u0027s yet to be determined.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":208,"aSentId":209},{"question":"When you look at President Obama\u0027s foreign policies since he became president, are you impressed by the way that he has conducted it?","answer":"I am, I am personally impressed.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":215,"aSentId":216},{"question":"But isn\u0027t it just weird that in the modern political world with the rhetoric as it is that he can\u0027t even get credit for something so straightforward?","answer":"Well, it\u0027s also a reminder in the great sweep of history that it\u0027s very hard to judge presidential decisions, presidential administrations at the time.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":263,"aSentId":264},{"question":"He\u0027s got a fight on his hands, doesn\u0027t he?","answer":"Well, he certainly has a fight on his hands.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":290,"aSentId":291},{"question":"When you look back at it, when you finished the book and shut the page, which of all the stories was the one that had the most personal connection for you?","answer":"I would say covering Dr. Martin Luther King in the Civil Rights Movement, which was my first big assignment for CBS News.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":322,"aSentId":323},{"question":"Do you really?","answer":"I do.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":331,"aSentId":332},{"question":"What do you think?","answer":"I get angry.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":333,"aSentId":334},{"question":"Will it ever properly recover from that day?","answer":"ATHER: Well, my personal opinion is we have not fully recovered.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":342,"aSentId":343},{"question":"Do you think American responded the right way?","answer":"I don\u0027t in this regard -- again, my personal opinion -- I think the sort of taking the emphasis off Iraq after the initial success and placing it on Afghanistan.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":352,"aSentId":353},{"question":"When you look back on the whole thing, knowing everything you now know, is there anything you would have done differently, with the great benefit of hindsight?","answer":"Well, we don\u0027t have the great benefit of hindsight.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":396,"aSentId":397},{"question":"Do you believe to this day those documents were genuine?","answer":"I do.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":407,"aSentId":408},{"question":"Have you ever had any conversation with President Bush since that?","answer":"Once.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":429,"aSentId":430},{"question":"Who was the one if you could choose one guy to lead your country?","answer":"Dwight Eisenhower would probably be my choice.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":447,"aSentId":448},{"question":"When you covered the Civil Rights Movement, did you ever imagine in your lifetime there would be a black president?","answer":"Not only did I not imagine it, we used to sit around in the shank of the evening over an adult beverage talking about civil rights.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":457,"aSentId":458},{"question":"May I answer that?","answer":"That wasn\u0027t a question.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":473,"aSentId":474},{"question":"Be that inquisitive, that interrogatory?","answer":"Frankly, I don\u0027t think any reporter could do it today.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":480,"aSentId":481},{"question":"When you take an overview, what do you think of modern journalism standards?","answer":"Well, American journalism is in crisis, in my opinion.","docId":"120501pmt","qSentId":493,"aSentId":494}]